      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming noise with no fan spin on your AC unit is a classic sign of a mechanical issue, like a seized motor or a capacitor failure. It's usually not immediately dangerous, but you should be cautious, especially around electrical components. I highly recommend calling a qualified HVAC technician to take a look, as trying to fix it yourself could be risky. They can diagnose whether it's a simple fix or something more serious, like a motor burnout.",
